r.d: teds (Tentative Extra Data Structures) is a collection of data structures and iterable functionality
r.n: * Breaking change: Change `Teds\Vector::__construct` to add an additional parameter `bool $preserveKeys = true`, and use the original keys of arrays/Traversables by default, throwing for non-integers and invalid integer offsets. (Similar to the behavior of SplFixedArray::fromArray) * Convert references to non-references when creating values from iterables. * Minor performance improvements of `Teds\Vector`
